('650', '1', 'Combine first 4 ingredients in processor. blend until mixture is finely chopped. With machine running, add oil through feed tube. puree until mixture is almost smooth.'),
('650', '2', 'Add crme frache. process until smooth.'),
('650', '3', 'Transfer sauce to small bowl. season with salt and pepper. DO AHEAD: Can be made 1 day ahead. Cover and chill. Rewhisk before using.'),
('651', '1', 'Sprinkle garlic with salt and mince to combine, then mash to a paste with flat side of chef''s knife. In a small bowl, mix paste with paprika, pepper, and 2 tbsp. oil.'),
('651', '2', 'Spread paste all over tri-tips. Wrap meat in plastic wrap and chill at least 24 hours and up to 2 days.'),
('651', '3', 'Preheat oven to 35'),
('651', '4', 'Scrape excess marinade from meat.'),
('651', '5', 'Heat remaining 1 tbsp. oil in a large, ovenproof frying pan over medium-high heat. Brown tri-tips on one side only, 3 to 4 minutes. Turn meat over in pan. then set in oven and roast until internal temperature reaches 125 for medium-rare, about 20 minutes.'),
('651', '6', 'Let meat rest, uncovered, on a cutting board 15 minutes.'),
('651', '7', 'Meanwhile, make salsa: Put all salsa ingredients in a food processor and pulse several times to combine into a rough sauce.'),
('651', '8', 'Slice each tri-tip thinly across the grain, rotating the meat to keep knife perpendicular to the grain (it changes direction on tri-tip).'),
('651', '9', 'Serve with salsa.'),
('655', '1', 'Combine all ingredients in a bowl, and toss gently until blended. Store in an airtight container in the refrigerator up to 1 week.'),
('655', '2', 'Serve at room temperature.'),
('657', '1', 'Preheat oven to 475F.'),
('657', '2', 'Combine first 3 ingredients in large bowl.'),
('657', '3', 'Add minced garlic and stir to blend. Season tomatomixture to taste with salt and pepper.'),
('657', '4', 'Arrange fish on rimmed baking sheet.'),
('657', '5', 'Brush both sides with 2 tablespoons oil. sprinkle with salt and pepper. Roast until just opaque in center, about 8 minutes.'),
('657', '6', 'Meanwhile, heat remaining 3 tablespoons oil in heavy large skillet over medium-high heat.'),
('657', '7', 'Add tomato mixture. Cook until tomatoes soften and sauce thickens, stirring occasionally, about 5 minutes. season with salt and pepper.'),
('657', '8', 'Toast bread. rub 1 side with cut side of halved garlic. Top with tomato sauce, basil leaves, fish, and more sauce.'),
('657', '9', 'Bon Appetit'),
('659', '1', 'To prepare mayonnaise, combine first 4 ingredients, stirring until smooth. cover and chill.'),
('659', '2', 'To prepare ravioli, place shiitake mushrooms in a food processor. pulse 6 times or until finely chopped.'),
('659', '3', 'Remove from processor.'),
('659', '4', 'Place button mushrooms in food processor. pulse 10 times or until finely chopped.'),
('659', '5', 'Heat a large nonstick skillet coated with cooking spray over medium-high heat.'),
('659', '6', 'Add mushrooms, shallots, thyme, and garlic. saut 15 minutes or until tender.'),
('659', '7', 'Add sherry. bring to a boil. Cook 8 minutes or until liquid almost evaporates.'),
('659', '8', 'Remove from heat. stir in Parmesan, salt, and pepper.'),
('659', '9', 'Place mushroom mixture in a bowl. let stand 10 minutes. Stir in sour cream.'),
('659', '10', 'Preheat oven to 42'),
('659', '11', 'Coat 2 baking sheets with cooking spray. Working with 1 wonton wrapper at a time (cover remaining wrappers to prevent drying), spoon 2 teaspoons mushroom mixture into center of wrapper. Moisten edges of wrapper with water. bring 2 opposite corners together. Press edges with a fork to seal, forming a triangle.'),
('659', '12', 'Place ravioli in a single layer on prepared baking sheets. spray tops lightly with cooking spray.'),
('659', '13', 'Bake at 425 for 14 minutes or until golden brown, turning once.'),
('659', '14', 'Serve with mayonnaise.'),
('660', '1', 'In a 2- to 3-quart pan or an electric skillet over medium heat, stir olive oil, butter, anchovies, and garlic, breaking up anchovies and garlic slightly with the back of a fork, until butter is melted and mixture is bubbling, about 5 minutes.'),
('660', '2', 'Remove from heat and let stand at least 10 minutes or up to 30 minutes.'),
('660', '3', 'Meanwhile, arrange the radicchio, endive, peppers, green onions, and mushrooms on a serving platter. Reheat butter mixture gently over low heat, then pour into a bowl or ramekin. Alternatively, pour into a 1 1/2- to 2-cup ceramic fondue pan or metal chafing dish in a water-bath jacket. Set over a votive candle or an ignited alcohol or canned solid-fuel flame. Adjust heat to lowest setting under fondue pan, to medium under chafing dish. Pass platter of vegetables and bread for guests to dip in warm bagna cauda.'),
